HONG KONG , July 1 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- Three barracks of the People 's Liberation Army -LRB- PLA -RRB- Garrison in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region -LRB- SAR -RRB- were opened to local residents Thursday on the occasion of the second anniversary of Hong Kong 's return to China .
The event , which is aimed at increasing understanding between the PLA troops and local residents , drew a large number of people from all walks of life early in the morning .
Visitors are arranged to watch a performance of martial arts and a display of the facilities and weapons of the troops in the three barracks for ground , naval and air forces at Stanley , Stonecutter Island and Shek Kong .
The garrison 's headquarters delivered a total of 10,000 tickets to social organizations and citizens last Sunday .
As tickets delivered for May 1 opening of the Stonecutter Island and Shek Kong barracks remain valid , about 20,000 people are expected to visit the PLA barracks on this opening day , according to a PLA officer .
The PLA troops came to station in Hong Kong after its return to China on July 1 , 1997 .
